<FontDataStyle>
<summary>
<div class="NOTE"><h5>NOTE</h5> <strong>Experimental</strong></div> The <strong><c>style</c></strong> read-only property of the <see cref="FontData"/> interface returns the style of the font face.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>This is the value used to select the style of the font you want to use, for example inside the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/font-style">font-style</see> property.</para><para>Examples include:</para>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.chrome.com/docs/capabilities/web-apis/local-fonts">Use advanced typography with local fonts</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face">@font-face</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/FontData/style"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>A string.</value>
</FontDataStyle>
